Three names have been shortlisted, for the position of the Vice Chancellor, Adamawa State University (ADSU) Mubi. Alhaji Auwal Tukur, Chairman of the Governing University (ADSU) Tuesday said, the names have been forwarded to Governor Ahmadu Fintiri for the appointment of substantive VC. Tukur noted that, most of the candidates were disqualified in the grounds of age, documentation and being member of the selection committee. He said the candidates were rated in 55 objective and 45 per cent subjective criteria, in collaboration with ministry of justice in the state. Henceforth incumbent VC would be disqualified from the race, as others were also disqualified for being member of the selection committee. “All the 25 candidates have academic capacity to be the VC of the institution.” Alhaji Umar Daware, Commissioner for Higher Education lauded the transparent conduct of the processes. Daware assured only the governor would announce the successful candidate for the position. Four female professors including Prof. Kaletapwa Farauta, the current acting vice chancellor of the university, Prof. Fati Astapawa Adamu, Prof. Jennifer Audu-Peter and Prof. Anah Malgwui contested. 